Sentencas: The anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) is constructed by a screen-printed double-layer cathode, an air-tight yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) as electrolyte, and a porous Ni-YSZ as anode substrate.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer

Sentencas: A thin Ni film is fabricated as an anode current collector layer to improve the performance of the SOFC.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer

Sentencas: The operation parameters are systematically investigated, such as feed rates of the reactants, operation temperature, contact pressure between current collectors and unit cell on the cell performance.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer

Sentencas: The SEM results show that the YSZ thin film is fully dense with a thickness of 8 mu m and exhibits the good compatibility between cathode and electrolyte layers.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer

Sentencas: The maximum power density of the cell with Ni current collector layer is 366 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer

Sentencas: This value is approximately 1.3 times higher than that of the cell without Ni layer.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer

Sentencas: According to the electrochemical results, the Ni current collector layer decreases the ohmic and polarization resistances.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer

Sentencas: The contact pressure results between cell and test housing show that cell performance efficiency is enhanced at the high current density region.
Titulo: Fabrication and characterization of the anode-supported solid oxide fuel cell with Ni current collector layer
